con:method.name: listTrackerBusinesses
con:method.con:description:
there are additional parameters which will work like mongo functions outer join: * $join: tracker.phonebook the other table * $joinTo: id phonebook.id * $joinFrom: business_details_nr business.business_details_nr
count: * $count: tracker.phonebook the other table returns the count of documents * $joinTo: id phonebook.id * $joinFrom: business_details_nr business.business_details_nr
regex search: * $regex: ware the text to search for * regexField: bus_name the field to search * regexSearchType: C How to match C = Contains, S = Starts with, E = Ends with
sort: * $sort: bus_name a field to sort on * sortDir: 1 1 = ascending sort -1 = descending sort

con:method.name: listPhonebook
con:method.con:description:
there are additional parameters which will work like mongo functions outer join: * $join: tracker.business the other table * $joinTo: id business.id * $joinFrom: business_details_nr phonebook.business_details_nr
count: * $count: tracker.business the other table returns the count of documents * $joinTo: id business.id * $joinFrom: business_details_nr phonebook.business_details_nr
regex search: * $regex: ware the text to search for * regexField: contact_details.contact_name the field to search * regexSearchType: C How to match C = Contains, S = Starts with, E = Ends with
sort: * $sort: bus_name a field to sort on * sortDir: 1 1 = ascending sort -1 = descending sort
pagination: * pagesize: 20 the bucket size * pagenum: 3 from 0, in pagesize units
